# Normalize all text files to LF in the repo and on checkout.
# The methodology is developed on WSL/Linux (LF); this prevents CRLF churn
# when files are touched by Windows editors or via DrvFs (/mnt) access,
# which previously showed up as a whole-tree "modified" diff (EOL only).
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect binary files and leave them untouched.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Archived live-model output is immutable, content-hashed evidence. Preserve
# intentional Markdown hard-break spaces instead of rewriting the transcript.
tests/fixtures/live-model-evidence/runs/**/output/*.md -whitespace
